programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Drought

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: El Niño
programme.desc: It is estimated that between 1997 and 1998, “El Niño” took the lives of 24,000 people and created a startling $34 billion (US) in economic damages worldwide. In this episode we explain what “El Niño” is.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Tsunamis

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Hurricanes

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Cyclones

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Mosquitoes

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Floods

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Iconic Buildings
programme.desc: In construction, only a few buildings can be groundbreaking. Vastly different in shape, size, and function, these diverse buildings prove there is no recipe for greatness, just the fundamental ingredients of vision, bravery, and imagination.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanoes
programme.desc: There are few sights on earth as compelling as a volcanic eruption. Volcanoes have the potential to cause death and widespread destruction in a heartbeat, but they also give rise to new life and ecosystems.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mega Cities
programme.desc: Mega Cities provide a bustling home to populations of over 10 million. Travel from the high-density living of Shanghai and Bangkok to the sprawling cities of Delhi and Mexico City, each the backdrop for dynamic cultures.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Lost Cities
programme.desc: Once powerful and populous centers of influence, these lost cities are providing clues to how our ancestors existed in the world and remind us that ancient civilizations were not so far removed from our own.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Archipelagos
programme.desc: The romantic notion of island life has always attracted us. Explore the histories, cultures, and unique ways of life on the World’s Greatest Archipelagos - clusters of islands that share common bonds of geography, geology, and genealogy.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Extreme Animals
programme.desc: Extreme Animals features environments hostile to humans, but havens to many animals. Witness gorgeous glow-worms, high flying condors, parched thorny devils, emperor penguins, and polar bears in this journey through life on the edge.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Marine Animals
programme.desc: From the surprises of colorful reef characters to effervescent penguins, killer sharks, and regal whales, dive into the places where nature reveals itself in some of its most marvelous and bizarre forms.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Sacred Sites
programme.desc: Ancient in architecture and detailed in design, these man-made masterpieces stand as testaments to the strength of human faith. These sites endure as a timeless reminder of resilience, respect, and the need to reflect.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Dutch Collaborator
programme.desc: Anton Adriaan Mussert, initially resisted Hitler’s anti-Semitism despite modeling his NSB party, even welcoming Jewish members. His failed attempt to kidnap Queen Wilhelmina led him into hiding, after which he collaborated in hopes of gaining power.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Jews Who Fought for Hitler
programme.desc: In Hitler’s Germany, those with Jewish ancestry faced harsh Nuremberg Laws. Full Jews faced death; Mischlinge endured discrimination, job bans. Some, like Helmut Schmidt, unaware of heritage, found protectors like Milch in high places.
programme.sub-title: The Jews Who Fought for Hitler

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Grand Mufti
programme.desc: The controversy surrounding Mohammad Amin al-Husayni, stems from his Nazi collaboration. He recruited Bosnian Muslims and advocated for a Palestinian homeland with Nazi help. His diaries reveal awareness of the Holocaust and anti-Semitic sentiments.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The IRA Conspiracy
programme.desc: During WWII, the IRA's "S Plan" aimed to bomb Britain, drawing German support to weaken the British. "Operation Green" and "Plan Kathleen" envisioned IRA aiding a German invasion of Northern Ireland, but both failed due to bungling and infighting.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Arajs Kommando
programme.desc: Viktor Arajs, a Latvian, played a significant role in the Holocaust, collaborating with the Nazis to eliminate Jews. Leading the Arajs Kommando, he orchestrated the killings of around 30,000 Jews. Arajs justified his actions as patriotic defense.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: Vidkun Quisling
programme.desc: Vidkun Quisling, once honored for diplomacy, turned traitor by collaborating with Nazis. His bid for power in Norway failed, relegated by Germans. Despite being named "fuehrer," his reign led to repression until his hanging post-Nazi defeat.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Devil's Due
programme.desc: During WWII, Greek Prime Ministers Tsolakoglou, Logothetopoulos, and Rallis collaborated with Nazi occupiers, imposing fees that caused a famine.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Croatian Collaborator
programme.desc: Croatia grapples with its fascist past through figures like Dinko Sakic, once hailed as a hero but later convicted of war crimes. Leading the notorious Jasenovac camp, Sakic oversaw brutal atrocities against inmates.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Belgian Collaborator
programme.desc: Leon Degrelle, a charismatic Belgian leader, joined the Nazis and led Die Wallonien on the Eastern Front. Despite no military background, he earned the Knight's Cross for valor. He recruited 4000 more for the SS, defending Berlin until April 1945.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: Traitor-in-Chief
programme.desc: Pierre Laval, once celebrated and later reviled, faced execution in 1945 for collaboration with the Nazis during Vichy France. Originally a socialist and pacifist, he fell into collaboration for power and to navigate the horrors of occupation.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: Hitler's Inside Man
programme.desc: Chaim Rumkowski, leader of the Lodz ghetto during WWII, believed cooperation with the Nazis could save lives, providing labor in exchange for food. This approach kept some semblance of community and culture alive amidst unimaginable horror.

programme.title: Hitler's Last Secrets: Fatal Liaison - The Strange Affair of Adolf and Eva
programme.desc: The protracted romance between Adolf Hitler and Eva Braun began in 1929 and ended in 1945 in the bunker under the ruins of the Chancellery.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: The fourth episode sees the Germans well and truly on the retreat and the Allies are able to successfully implement operation Husky: the landing on Sicily.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: The third episode opens with Rommel’s second offensive in North Africa.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: The second episode starts on the morning of the 22nd of June 1941 when the Germans launched operation Barbarossa, the code name for the invasion of the Soviet Union.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: This first part of the series introduces the first tanks being deployed on the battlefields in northern France during WWI and describes the devastating effect these steel monsters had on an infantry confronted with them for the very first time.

programme.title: Gestapo: Hitler's Secret Police
programme.desc: Hermann Goering’s Secret State Police were tasked to arrest and torture confessions and information from supposed enemies of the Reich.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Waffen-SS
programme.desc: The Waffen-SS: Masqueraded as military excellence, the reality was very different. Recruits were poorly trained and remorse was nonexistent, as SS troops killed mercilessly.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The SS Death Head's Unit
programme.desc: The SS Death Head's Unit: Tasked with guarding concentration camps, this unit's actions knew no bounds, and, despite their heinous acts, still attended social gatherings.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945
programme.desc: Unrepentant: The SS and Its Myth After 1945: Drawing a line to the present, the atrocities of the SS are beyond all doubt, yet, there is a cult surrounding 'old comrades' today.
programme.sub-title: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: Rise of The Bomber
programme.desc: Rise of the Bomber: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: War Without Boundaries
programme.desc: War Without Boundaries: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: The Means To Victory
programme.desc: The Means to Victory: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: The World At War
programme.desc: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: By Night & By Day
programme.desc: By Night & By Day: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: Terror of The World
programme.desc: Terror of the World: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Einsatzgruppen: The Nazi Death Squads: Mass Graves
programme.desc: This first episode provides context for when, how and why the mobile death squads, or EZG, were established.

programme.title: Einsatzgruppen: The Nazi Death Squads: Judenfrei
programme.desc: In December 1941, after the EZG’s intervention, Romania, Bulgaria, Hungary and the Baltic states are declared 'Judenfrei': free of Jews.

programme.title: Einsatzgruppen: The Nazi Death Squads: Funeral Pyres
programme.desc: Faced with the advancing Soviet troops, Nazi Germany decided to have the bodies of the death camp victims dug up and burned in graves

programme.title: Einsatzgruppen: The Nazi Death Squads: Time Of Reckoning
programme.desc: After being judged at the Nuremberg trials, the majority of those responsible for the murder of nearly 1.5 million Jews would walk free in the 1950s

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922
programme.desc: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922: In the wake of the First World War, Adolf Hitler identifies Benito Mussolini as his model and has one ultimate goal: to gain power in Germany.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928
programme.desc: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928: Hitler appears to be eliminated after his failed putsch in 1923. Discover how the Nazi movement used democracy's tolerance in Germany to come back.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Democracy without Democrats 1929-1933
programme.desc: Democracy Without Democrats 1929-1933: A protest turns into a racist and anti-Jewish movement during the 1920s and the NSDAP use emotions to gain the loyalty of the people.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Racial State 1933-1934
programme.desc: The Racial State 1933-1934: President Hindenburg suspends freedom of speech and Hitler comes to power in 1933. The first concentration camps for political opponents are set up.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Hidden in Plain Sight 1935-1938
programme.desc: Hidden In Plain Sight 1935-1938: In 1934, Hitler's government is firmly in the saddle. Most Germans support Hitler's anti-Jewish policy and the regime's terror soon escalates.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Up in Flames 1936-1940
programme.desc: Up in Flames 1936-1940: At the end of 1939, the German Army invades Poland. Examine how Hitler succeeded in pushing through his rearmament and war plans relatively unhindered.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942
programme.desc: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942: In the shadow of the war, the Nazi regime gradually advances its "final solution to the Jewish problem", culminating in the Holocaust.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Railway Bridges
programme.desc: Railway bridges fascinate through different construction methods from masonry, truss-beam bridges to steel-concrete arch bridge. Heavier loads, faster speeds, more frequently: trains speed over bridges and the maintenance teams face ever larger challenges

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Steel Bridges
programme.desc: Steel bridges are extremely durable and multifunctional, fascinating not only due to its gigantic size but also because of the army of workers keeping the bridges in shape: whether on the historical landmark in Sydney or ultramodern mega bridges in China.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Road Bridges
programme.desc: Road bridges: gigantic constructions of modern road traffic. Europa and Ganter Bridge, Öresund bridge, Sunshine Skyway and Viaduct de Millau.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Suspension Bridges
programme.desc: Suspension bridges – impressively wide and stretched high over supporting cables or stay cables. The landscape-shaping icons: The superlative Golden Gate, Akashi Kaikyo, Aizaih, El Baluarte and Russky Bridge.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Power Generator
programme.desc: A three hundred and ninety ton giant on a daring journey: A team of German heavy-lift-specialists have to transport a generator from a disused coal plant to its new operation site 120 kilometers away.

programme.title: Mega Transports: ITER Magnet
programme.desc: This giant magnet will revolutionize the world and energy production in the future. The world's largest nuclear fusion reactor is currently under construction in southern France.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Drilling Rig
programme.desc: A brand-new oil rig, worth 500 million dollar, has to go from South Korea to Europe. The problem is that it is too gigantic for a heavy transport vessel. The solution is to tow it.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Siberian Ice Road
programme.desc: A Mega Transport on one of the most dangerous roads in the world. The Siberian Ice Road. It doesn't forgive mistakes. It's treacherous. And unpredictable.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Giant Antenna
programme.desc: South America. The chelonian Atacama Desert is home to the world's largest radio telescope Atacama Large Millimeter Array Observatory, also known as ALMA.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Mining Truck
programme.desc: If a transporter needs to be transported, if 176 wheels aren't enough to carry its weight and if the load weighs twice as much as the transporter... Then it must be the mother of all mega transports!

programme.title: Mega Transports: Wind Park
programme.desc: A wind park needs to get from Europe to Asia. Over two thousand tons of highly sensitive and valuable cargo. On one of the world's largest heavy lift vessels.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Gigantic Autoliner
programme.desc: A transport to the other side of the globe. The Höegh Trapper is the largest automobile transporter in the world. Two hundred meters long, thirty-six meters wide.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Biggest Containership
programme.desc: When the first ship of the brand-new OOCL-fleet gets underway, more cargo is moved at one time than anywhere else in the world and ever before.

programme.title: Mega Transports: AutoClav
programme.desc: A unique mega transport made of steel and titanium with a special purpose: to extract tons of gold. This so-called autoclave is the biggest of its kind. Its weight: over one thousand tons.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Superyachts
programme.desc: Transporting a ship by a ship - this becomes necessary when the super-rich want their super yacht available on the other side of the world, but do not want to sail it there themselves.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Villagemove
programme.desc: Everyone knows it: Housemoving is a lot of work, requires excellent planning and costs time and money. Just imagine how it must be if you are moving an entire village - as a whole.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Conveyance of the Norwegian Joy
programme.desc: Meyer Werft in Germany is one of the biggest shipbuilders in the world. But it's problem is as big as the ships it builds: the coast and sea are 50 kilometres away.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Antonov
programme.desc: A giant of the skies - the Antonov AN-124-100M-150. Worldwide the biggest production cargo aircraft of all time. No aircraft can transport more goods than the Russian giant.

programme.title: Alien Reptilian Legacy
programme.desc: Researchers reveal the presence of a supreme and nefarious interdimensional intelligence that has been manipulating mankind for centuries. Interviews with experiencers and alien abductees expose a sinister agenda behind the alien presence on Earth.

programme.title: Roswell: The Untold Truth
programme.desc: Major Jesse Marcel investigates strange debris found in 1947, despite being told it's a weather balloon.

programme.title: Cover Ups Conspiracy: The Chinese Spy Balloon
programme.desc: Objects shot down in US/Canada airspace. Pentagon feigns ignorance. Alien involvement?

programme.title: The Witnesses: Ancient Alien Encounters
programme.desc: Contactee, sighter, and abductee share similar and different experiences with beings from other dimensions, leaving a lasting mark of their presence.

programme.title: Alien Invasion: Are We Ready?: Episode 2
programme.desc: A continued look at how an alien attack could unfold and whether human beings would be able to resist such an attack, either in the short term or in the long term.

programme.title: Alien Invasion: Are We Ready?: Episode 1
programme.desc: Aliens attacking Earth is the stuff of sci-fi stories, but what if it really happened? Top scientists, military strategists and authors war-game an extraordinary alien invasion scenario.

programme.title: The Hills' Abduction: The Zeta Reticuli Incident
programme.desc: Barney & Betty Hill's abduction and the Zeta reticuli incident explored.

programme.title: Alien Global Threat
programme.desc: New evidence reveals that world governments have had a pact with aliens for decades and that human abductions are being allowed by government and military factions.

programme.title: Ancient Alien Question
programme.desc: Join Philip Coppens, star of the History Channel's "Ancient Aliens" series, as he provides proof that UFO's helmed by Extraterrestrials from other worlds came to Earth millennia ago.

programme.title: Deep Sea Aliens
programme.desc: Explore the mysteries of the deep sea: underwater anomalies, alien abductions, USOs, and unexplained cases that defy our understanding.

programme.title: Linda Napolitano: The Alien Abduction of the Century
programme.desc: Linda Napolitano's 1989 alien abduction is the abduction case of the century.

programme.title: Unsolved Mysteries: UFO Odyssey

programme.title: 30 Insane UFO Encounters
programme.desc: A review of the 30 most insane UFO encounters for your eyes delight and its up to you to make your own mind up, if these amazing encounters could be the real deal or one big elaborate hoax

programme.title: Alien Crash Retrievals
programme.desc: Learn the shocking truth about extraterrestrial beings on planet Earth. World governments and military factions are not only aware of the Alien presence; they may be in communication with alien races.

programme.title: Aliens Against Nuclear War: Edgar Mitchell
programme.desc: 12 moonwalkers claim ET visited Earth, govt covered it up. Aliens stopped nuclear war. Crazy or worth hearing more?

programme.desc: Temagami is home of some of the oldest rocks on the face of the planet, old growth pine forests, clear deep lakes, and boasts artifacts and stone drawings dating as far back as 6000 B.C.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: From the very beginning, the men face a life and death struggle, as the fierce currents of the Pacific Ocean force Bear to drop them 75 meters off the island.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: These women will be utterly alone for six weeks, left to film everything themselves. So when stripped of the luxuries and conveniences of 21st-century living, will these women have the skills and mental strength to survive and rival the male islanders?

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: Mild-mannered paramedic, Barney Strange, comes to the rescue of the group by catching and feeding the men a tasty but unusual supper. Just five days in and the group has reached a breaking point.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: This time the survival challenge is harder than before, as they attempt to survive entirely on their own wits for six weeks in the height of the tropical storm season.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: The men face a life and death struggle with the island's most fearsome predator. Two weeks in and the men are in rapid physical decline. Despite their best efforts to hunt and fish, they haven't yet managed to catch themselves a substantial meal.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: It’s Lauren’s 25th birthday, but there’s little to celebrate. Two castaways have already abandoned the women’s island due to the extreme conditions, since being dropped in the Pacific seven days ago. The 12 remaining are desperately dehydrated.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: It’s four days since then men killed a crocodile, and they haven’t been able to repeat their success. Most of the meager meals they are eating are coming from Vic, who is the only member of the group to have mastered his improvised fishing rod.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: The extreme conditions on the island are taking their toll on the 11 remaining women and they are now on the brink of starvation. They are living on an extremely low-calorie diet, surviving on snails and scraps of scavenged yucca and coconut.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: The 10 remaining women are entering the dangerous medical territory. It’s more important than ever that they keep up their food and water supply otherwise they risk long term damage to their vital organs.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: In this episode, the emergency evacuation team is called in when 36-year old Will falls off a cliff onto rocks, badly injuring himself.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: The women are starving as they enter their sixth and final week on The Island. Having plundered all the resources in the vicinity of their beach, the group is now looking to the ocean to sustain them.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: In this final episode, after five weeks on the island, the men are struggling to find enough to eat as the island's already depleted resources fail to deliver the coconuts and limpets that have become their staple diet.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: The 1969 flight of Apollo 11, which landed two American astronauts on the Moon, as seen through the eyes of the astronauts, mission controllers, engineers, and designers who made it happen.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: The X-1 jet breaks the sound barrier; the X-43 Scramjet flies at Mach 7; U-2 and SR-71 Cold War spy planes; flying Wing bombers; the new F/A Raptor.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Adrenaline runs high when Adam Richman visits the factory where Yamaha makes ATVs, WaveRunners and more; an inside look at a company built to get people sky-high in paramotors; amusement park Diggerland USA; mech-suits; submarine built for two.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Testing the breaking points of vehicles and crash test dummies; firing rounds at bulletproof glass; breaching a safe; the breaking points of steel and concrete.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: All life-forms and modern technology are built on a foundation of carbon; the steel industry; coal-fired power plants; graphite pencils; a charcoal water filter; diamonds.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Some machines built for sheer spectacle.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: The evolution of the assembly line, which has produced billions of products, from toys to Boeing 747s, cheaply and quickly; Americans overcome prejudices toward blacks and women in factories during World War II; a family of auto assembly workers.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: A machine-press stamps out an entire car body; a chain-saw cuts through rock; a telescope glimpses the ends of the known universe; a rock crusher; Keck Observatory.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Thomas Alva Edison successfully files more than 1,000 patents.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Jonas Salk is catapulted to fame after discovering the vaccine to prevent poliomyelitis, a disease that had disabled and killed thousands.
programme.sub-title: The Search for the Polio Vaccine

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Each flip of an electric-light switch attests to the genius of Nikola Tesla, creator of the alternating current (AC) system; the Tesla coil; energy-efficient bulbs.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: U.S. military fighter jets.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Wind tunnel; flight simulators; mining machine; IMAX technology.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: A large factory-fishing boat hunts down, catches and processes 300 tons of Alaskan pollock each day in the Bering Sea; the crew reveals the inner workings of one of the most sophisticated and complex vessels afloat.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Amazing, ingenious and ultrasturdy shelters, machines, containers, and materials help to ensure the continuation of society.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Using fertilizer to make crops and grass grow.

programme.title: Modern Marvels

programme.title: Christmas Festival of Ice
programme.desc: When Emma finds out that her beloved ice-sculpting contest, part of her hometown's Christmas festival, has been canceled, she springs into action.

programme.title: Christmas She Wrote
programme.desc: When Kayleigh, a romance writer, has her column cancelled right before Christmas, she heads home to reconnect with her family. Kayleigh gets an unexpected visit from the man who cancelled her column.

programme.title: A Godwink Christmas: Miracle of Love
programme.desc: Brought together by community service, Eric and Joy find new purpose at Christmas. As they help a family rebuild their home, coincidences and a medical miracle lead them to believe in destiny.

programme.title: A Godwink Christmas: Second Chance, First Love
programme.desc: After 15 years, Pat moves home from Hawaii with his two sons and through a series of coincidences, or Godwinks, ends up stuck in traffic next to his high school sweetheart, Margie at Christmas.

programme.title: Small Town Christmas
programme.desc: A high-flying female novelist from New York takes a trip to the small town that inspired her latest best-seller.

programme.title: A Snow Capped Christmas
programme.desc: When champion figure skater Claire becomes injured she is sent to a rehabilitation center in the snowy mountains where she meets and falls for a local ice fisherman who shows her there is more to life than competition.

programme.title: Let it Snow
programme.desc: Apollo Resorts buys small businesses, tears them down, and builds giant tourist traps in their place. But when Stephanie Beck shows up at Snow Valley Lodge, she gets swept up in the Christmas spirit.

programme.title: Inn For Christmas
programme.desc: Mandy Leeds doesn’t get back to her small northern hometown much, but this year her Gram has finally convinced her to come home for Christmas.

programme.title: My Grown Up Christmas List
programme.desc: Taylor and Luke have a special bond that grows between them after several Christmases spent together and apart.

programme.desc: To hear Bill Mason tell about the making of this feature film (he is also the narrator) is to share with him his affection for his camera-quarry: the big northern timber wolves and pure-white Arctic wolves.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Needles And Pins
programme.desc: In this film about a factory seamstress, there is the substitution of glamor for genuine job satisfaction and advancement. The film was made in 1955.

programme.title: Churchills Island
programme.desc: A classic presentation of the strategy of the Battle of Britain, the film shows, with penetrating clarity, the relationship of the various forces that went to make up the island's defenses. The first NFB film to win an Oscar.

programme.title: Paul Kane Goes West
programme.desc: in the mid-1800s, Paul Kane painted the northwest, Indigneous Peopless, Chiefs, ceremonies, war parties, buffalo hunts, rapids and waterfalls. In this film his paintings are projected with lighting that brings to life every glowing detail.

programme.title: Best Time Of My Life Portraits Of Women In Mid-Life, The
programme.desc: An upbeat, positive film about a group of women dealing with mid-life and menopause. The women come from a wide range of backgrounds, careers and lifestyles, it effectively dispels popular myths and fears about life during and after menopause.

programme.title: Alphee Of The Stars
programme.desc: Alphée of the Stars puts the spotlight on a most unusual girl. With patience and tenderness, a father – who believes in schools that embrace diversity and do not discriminate – challenges our assumptions and reveals an unknown world.

programme.title: What Walaa Wants
programme.desc: Raised in a West Bank refugee camp while her mother was in prison, Walaa is determined to become a policewoman in the Palestinian Security Forces—not easy for a girl who breaks all the rules.

programme.title: Under The Willow Tree Pioneer Chinese Women In Canada
programme.desc: Explore the untold history of Chinese Canadian women, from their courageous journeys to the challenges they faced in Canada. Through photos, recollections, and narration by Dora Nipp, this film captures their resilience and cultural legacy.

programme.title: Rusting World
programme.desc: The scene is a desolate landscape that reveals no signs of life. Out of the stillness emerge two opposing factions, both wanting possession of a shiny object. This allegorical film suggests a decaying world created by greed

programme.title: Junior
programme.desc: Reflecting our society, the world of junior hockey is obsessed with competition. Taking in one complete season with the Baie-Comeau Drakkar, this film reveals the daily lives of managers and players on this Quebec Major Junior Hockey League team.

programme.title: Kevin Alec
programme.desc: In the mountainous country near Lillooet, eleven-year-old Kevin Alec of the Fountain Indian Reserve learns to make fishnets with his grandfather, and skin and tan hides with his aunt. Will he eventually abandon his traditional way of life?

programme.title: Canada Vignettes Log Drivers Waltz
programme.desc: A young girl who loves to dance and is ready to marry chooses a log driver over his more well-to-do, land-loving competition. Driving logs down the river has made him the best dancing partner to be found.

programme.title: Totem Talk
programme.desc: Urban Indigenous teens embark on a surreal journey guided by a magical raven, encountering animated totem pole characters and exploring Northwest First Nation culture's significance. Featuring insights from artist J. Bradley Hunt.

programme.title: Beautiful Lennard Island
programme.desc: Steven Holland, age ten, is the son of the lighthouse-keeper in charge of Lennard Island, a tiny place west of Vancouver Island. He takes us on a tour and dispels any ideas we might have that living in isolation is boring.

programme.title: Sylvies Story
programme.desc: The film shows Sylvie in a Montréal transition house, highlighting the hurdles of violence, loneliness, and scarcity. It emphasizes sharing experiences and transition houses' support in connecting victims with legal and social aid.

programme.title: Chile Obstinate Memory
programme.desc: A generation of young Chileans has grown up with no knowledge of the facts surrounding the military coup of September 11, 1973. Now, Patricio Guzmán returns to Chile, after 23 years. The time has come to reveal the long-forgotten truth.

programme.title: When The Day Breaks
programme.desc: In "When the Day Breaks," Ruby finds solace in unexpected places after witnessing a stranger's death. Through deft humor and detailed animation, it explores the interconnectedness of urban life, capturing the promise and fragility of each new day.

programme.title: Notmans World
programme.desc: William Notman was a man of rare talent. Photography was still in its infancy when he opened his first studio--in Montréal--in the late 1850s. He rapidly turned his art, and a budding technology, into a highly successful business.

programme.title: Lipsett Diaries
programme.desc: Lipsett Diaries is a descent into the maelstrom of anguish that tormented famed Canadian experimental filmmaker Arthur Lipsett, who died prematurely at age 49.

programme.title: Nobody Waved Good-Bye
programme.desc: A story of teenage conflict--the predicament of a youth who rebels against his parents' middle-class goals and conventions but finds the world, away from home and high school, a cold place to go it alone.

programme.title: Lay Down Your Heart
programme.desc: An accomplished artist, a lifelong performer and a person with Down syndrome, Niall McNeil has built a unique family tree of blood and chosen relations made up of his closest friends and collaborators.

programme.title: Vendetta Song
programme.desc: Filmmaker Eylem Kaftan unravels her aunt's 30-year-old murder mystery in Kurdish Turkey. "Vendetta Song" explores customs and Eylem's quest for closure amid political instability and potential retribution.

programme.title: Weihnachtswunderland
programme.desc: Die Weihnachtszeit in New York ist für die erfolglose Künstlerin Heidi Neill alles andere als wundervoll.

programme.title: Der Weihnachts-Song
programme.desc: Budgetkürzungen zwingen zwei New Yorker Hochschulen zu fusionieren. Ein Musiklehrer und eine Lehrerin konkurrieren im größten Weihnachts-Song Wettbewerb des Landes um die Arbeitsstelle des...

programme.title: Return To Christmas Creek
programme.desc: Eine junge Chefin kehrt in ihre Heimatstadt zurück, um die Bedeutung von Weihnachten wiederzuentdecken.

programme.title: Ich bin nicht bereit für Weihnachten
programme.desc: Hollys energiegeladenes, karriereorientiertes Leben gerat vollig aus den Fugem, als sie feststellt, dass sie nicht mehr lugen kann, weil der Weihnachtsmann ihrer Nichte Anna einen besonderen Wunsch erfullt hat.

programme.title: Christmas Encore
programme.desc: Charlotte Lacy ist eine verzweifelte Schauspielerin, die die Hauptrolle in einer Produktion von "A Christmas Carol" ergattert. Sie und der Regisseur haben jedoch viele unterschiedliche kreative Vorstellungen.

programme.title: Mistelzweige küsst man nicht
programme.desc: Zu Weihnachten kehrt Darcy nach Hause zurück und läuft dort ihrem Highschool-Erzfeind Luke über den Weg. Als beide bei der Vorbereitung einer weihnachtlichen Wohltätigkeitsgala helfen, erkennen sie, dass ihre bisherige Abneigung womöglich voreilig war.

programme.title: Christmas in Boston
programme.desc: Gina und Seth sind seit ihrer Kindheit Brieffreunde, haben sich aber noch nie getroffen. Als sie sich endlich dazu entschließen, sich zu treffen, braucht es allerdings ein wenig Weihnachtszauber, um ihre Liebe füreinander aufzudecken.

programme.title: Broadcasting Christmas
programme.desc: Als ihr Sendeparyner beschliebt, Amerikas beliebteste Morgensendung zu verlassen, kundigt Veronika Daniels an, dass sie ihren neuen Co-Moderator aus einer Handvoll Kandidten auswahlen wird, zu denen auch Charlie Fisher.

programme.title: Christmas Encore
programme.desc: Charlotte Lacy ist eine verzweifelte Schauspielerin, die die Hauptrolle in einer Produktion von "A Christmas Carol" ergattert. Sie und der Regisseur haben jedoch viele unterschiedliche kreative Vorstellungen.

programme.title: Das perfekte Weihnachten
programme.desc: Benjamin will mit seiner Musikkarriere endlich richtig durchstarten und gibt dafür seine Aufnahmen dem Rapper J-Jizzy. Doch zunächst muss Benjamin sich noch seinem Job als Weihnachtsmann in einem Einkaufszentrum widmen...

programme.title: Mein Weihnachtstraum
programme.desc: Um sich vor der gefürchteten Besitzerin eines Kaufhauses in Paris zu beweisen, bittet Managerin Christina den kürzlich gefeuerten Kurt um Hilfe in der Weihnachtszeit. Als die beiden sich näher kommen, muss Christina eine schwere Wahl treffen...

programme.title: Weihnachten mit Hindernissen
programme.desc: Vicky und Jason haben sich schon längst getrennt. Aber ihre beiden Kinder bringen sie dazu, die Weihnachtsferien gemeinsam zu verbringen. Als dann auch noch Vickys Boss und Jasons Assistentin auftauchen, wird es immer turbulenter...

programme.title: Die Nanny
programme.desc: Fran hofft auf ein Wunder, als Maxwell, Grace und C.C. nach einem Autounfall vermisst werden.

programme.title: Freezing Cold Fails
programme.desc: It's not easy to look cool in cold conditions when ice and snow cause all kinds of clumsy fails!

programme.title: PAA Christmas
programme.desc: People Are Awesome Christmas edition.

programme.title: Ein Wunder am Weihnachtssee
programme.desc: Der 16-jährige Bobby macht auf dem benachbarten See eines Abends eine erstaunliche Entdeckung: Eine hell beleuchtete Eishockeypiste, die von einem Mann bearbeitet wird, der sich ihm als Weihnachtsmann vorstellt.

programme.title: Alone for Christmas
programme.desc: Wenn eine Familie an Heiligabend das Haus von Oma besucht, lässt sie ihren Hund allein zu Hause. Und wenn Einbrecher versuchen, die Geschenke unter dem Baum hervorzuholen, um sie zu stoppen.

programme.title: Die Suche nach dem Weihnachtsmann
programme.desc: Selbst an den kältesten Orten kann der Weihnachts-Zauber die Herzen erwärmen. Dieses Zeichentrick-Abenteuer voller klasse Figuren, mit tollen neuen Liedern und einer rührenden Story handelt von Freundschaft, Familie und der wunderbarsten Jahreszeit.

programme.title: Ein Weihnachtsmärchen

programme.title: Desejo de Natal
programme.desc: Sem dinheiro e abandonada pelo marido com três filhos, Martha não está tendo o melhor fim de ano da sua vida. Mas ela muda de cidade e redescobre a esperança quando encontra um emprego e uma rede de apoio em uma pacata lanchonete de interior.

programme.title: Natal Feliz
programme.desc: Após a morte de seu pai, um menino cria um vínculo especial com o cachorro de um vizinho e aprende a ser um homem ajudando seus avós durante uma tempestade de inverno.

programme.title: Bebê a Bordo no Natal
programme.desc: Na sequência de “Um Ano Depois Daquele Natal”, nem todo mundo parece estar animado para o Natal da Família Chandler.

programme.title: O Verdadeiro Sentido do Amor

programme.title: O Natal Prometido
programme.desc: Quando uma queda de energia causa pânico em uma loja, eles são separados um do outro. Cada um sentiu uma conexão com o outro, mas eles não têm como se reconectar. Com a aproximação do Natal, nem Kim nem Theo podem esquecer o outro.

programme.title: Lucia e o Cristal Mágico
programme.desc: Lucia é a primeira menina da Escola Internacional de Natal. Quando seu melhor amigo, Oscar, é acusado de roubar o cristal mágico do Rei Inverno, que alimenta a máquina atual, Lucia se propõe a provar a inocência dele.

programme.title: Festividades do Chocolate Quente
programme.desc: Colette dirige uma cafetaria conhecida pelo seu chocolate quente secreto e famoso. Marcus, um novo dono de sobremesa, começa a atrair os clientes da Colette, ela está determinada a expô-lo.

programme.title: Coming Home For Christmas
programme.desc: Kate tiene la gran idea de reunir para Navidad a su familia separada y volver a su antigua casa. El problema es que alguien vive allí y no es muy amable.

programme.title: Shelby
programme.desc: Shelby es un perro sin dueño que tiene por costumbre fugarse de la perrera cada vez que tiene la oportunidad. Durante una de sus escapadas conoce a Jake, un niño que sueña con ser un gran mago, y se hacen amigos inseparables.

programme.title: A Christmas Break
programme.desc: Cuando la maestra Addison Tate se entera de que su escuela va a cerrar, decide hacer que esta Navidad sea especial para sus alumnos. Solicita la ayuda de Danny y la química entre ellos se reaviva cuando salvan la escuela justo antes de Nochebuena.

programme.title: A Christmas Karen
programme.desc: Karen es una mujer de mediana edad que, debido a su actitud exigente y arrogante, ha alienado a sus amigos y familia. Un día, Karen recibe una visita por parte de unos espíritus no convencionales.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: Ballet para Navidad
programme.desc: Un video de Michel aprendiendo ballet con su hija lo convierte en el soltero más codiciado de la ciudad.

programme.title: Fabric of Christmas, The
programme.desc: Liam, un bombero, y Amy, una profesora de acolchado, se unen para hacer una colcha navideña para la boda de la hermana de Liam, pero su romance se ve amenazado por el plan de Liam de viajar a Sudamérica.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: La cabaña de Navidad
programme.desc: Mary se va de vacaciones a las montañas con su novio. De camino, encuentran a una niña que se había torcido el tobillo, y que casualmente es la hija de un antiguo amigo de su infancia.

programme.title: Coming Home For Christmas
programme.desc: Kate tiene la gran idea de reunir para Navidad a su familia separada y volver a su antigua casa. El problema es que alguien vive allí y no es muy amable.

programme.title: Shelby
programme.desc: Shelby es un perro sin dueño que tiene por costumbre fugarse de la perrera cada vez que tiene la oportunidad. Durante una de sus escapadas conoce a Jake, un niño que sueña con ser un gran mago, y se hacen amigos inseparables.

programme.title: A Christmas Break
programme.desc: Cuando la maestra Addison Tate se entera de que su escuela va a cerrar, decide hacer que esta Navidad sea especial para sus alumnos. Solicita la ayuda de Danny y la química entre ellos se reaviva cuando salvan la escuela justo antes de Nochebuena.

programme.title: A Christmas Karen
programme.desc: Karen es una mujer de mediana edad que, debido a su actitud exigente y arrogante, ha alienado a sus amigos y familia. Un día, Karen recibe una visita por parte de unos espíritus no convencionales.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: Ballet para Navidad
programme.desc: Un video de Michel aprendiendo ballet con su hija lo convierte en el soltero más codiciado de la ciudad.

programme.title: Fabric of Christmas, The
programme.desc: Liam, un bombero, y Amy, una profesora de acolchado, se unen para hacer una colcha navideña para la boda de la hermana de Liam, pero su romance se ve amenazado por el plan de Liam de viajar a Sudamérica.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: La cabaña de Navidad
programme.desc: Mary se va de vacaciones a las montañas con su novio. De camino, encuentran a una niña que se había torcido el tobillo, y que casualmente es la hija de un antiguo amigo de su infancia.

programme.title: Coming Home For Christmas
programme.desc: Kate tiene la gran idea de reunir para Navidad a su familia separada y volver a su antigua casa. El problema es que alguien vive allí y no es muy amable.

programme.title: Shelby
programme.desc: Shelby es un perro sin dueño que tiene por costumbre fugarse de la perrera cada vez que tiene la oportunidad. Durante una de sus escapadas conoce a Jake, un niño que sueña con ser un gran mago, y se hacen amigos inseparables.

programme.title: A Christmas Break
programme.desc: Cuando la maestra Addison Tate se entera de que su escuela va a cerrar, decide hacer que esta Navidad sea especial para sus alumnos. Solicita la ayuda de Danny y la química entre ellos se reaviva cuando salvan la escuela justo antes de Nochebuena.

programme.title: A Christmas Karen
programme.desc: Karen es una mujer de mediana edad que, debido a su actitud exigente y arrogante, ha alienado a sus amigos y familia. Un día, Karen recibe una visita por parte de unos espíritus no convencionales.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: Ballet para Navidad
programme.desc: Un video de Michel aprendiendo ballet con su hija lo convierte en el soltero más codiciado de la ciudad.

programme.title: Fabric of Christmas, The
programme.desc: Liam, un bombero, y Amy, una profesora de acolchado, se unen para hacer una colcha navideña para la boda de la hermana de Liam, pero su romance se ve amenazado por el plan de Liam de viajar a Sudamérica.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: La cabaña de Navidad
programme.desc: Mary se va de vacaciones a las montañas con su novio. De camino, encuentran a una niña que se había torcido el tobillo, y que casualmente es la hija de un antiguo amigo de su infancia.

programme.title: Wilde Schönheiten: Der Oman
programme.desc: Die arabische Halbinsel ist von unerbittlicher Wüste mit unerträglichen Temperaturen bedeckt. Die Landschaft erscheint unbewohnbar. Hinter dem feindlichen Äußeren verbirgt sich jedoch ein reiches Ökosystem mit großer Artenvielfalt.

programme.title: Mitten im Südafrika
programme.desc: Unsere Tour beginnt an der namibianischen Grenze. Andreas Erwartungen sind groß. Südafrika ist ein Land der Gegensätze und am stärksten macht sich das an der Westküste bemerkbar

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Wir stehen alle auf irgendjemandes Speiseplan. Deshalb hat sich die in der Natur ausgebildete Spezialisierung auf eine bestimmte Beute und Nahrung auf so faszinierende Art weiterentwickelt. Fressen, ähnlich wie Sex, bereitet allen Tieren Freude, wenngleich in geringerer Intensivität.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Die am meisten verbreitete Beziehung zwischen Lebewesen ist die von Räuber und Opfer. Aber es gibt auch andere, zum Beispiel gewaltfreie Beziehungen und viele andere, die für beide Seiten von Nutzen sind. Manchmal bleiben Tiere unterschiedlicher Gattungen ihr ganzes Leben zusammen.

programme.title: Agakröten: Die Eroberung
programme.desc: Der Film untersucht eine der größten Umweltkatastrophen in Australien, den unaufhaltbaren Marsch der Agakröte. Wir Menschen haben weltweit unser Ökosystem unwiderruflich verändert, und diese Geschichte ist von universeller Bedeutung.

programme.title: Naledi – Ein Elefantenleben
programme.desc: Eine Tierfarm in der Wildnis Botswanas: Die Elefantenkuh Niki ist hochschwanger. Seit Wochen wird die Geburt ihres Babys sehnlichst erwartet. In einer sternklaren Nacht ist es soweit, ein kleines Elefantenmädchen wird geboren

programme.desc: Im entlegenen Amazonasgebiet sucht Jeremy Wade nach einem Raubtier, das sich nicht mit der Angel fangen lässt.

programme.title: Der Hoplias aimara
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade sucht in Japan nach dem Kappa, einem Fisch, um den sich viele Legenden ranken.

programme.title: Der Riesenwels
programme.desc: Der Biologe und Extremangler Jeremy Wade geht den Gerüchten über einen menschenfressenden Wels nach.

programme.title: Der rote Pacu
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade sucht in Neuseeland nach einer gefährlichen Kreatur, die vor 200 Jahren entdeckt wurde.

programme.desc: Extremangler Jeremy Wade begibt sich auf der Suche nach einem Killerfisch tief nach Mittelamerika.

programme.desc: Der Extremangler Jeremy Wade begibt sich auf eine Mission in Guyana in Südamerika.

programme.title: Süßwasserhaie
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade geht dem Mythos des Süßwasserhais nach.

programme.title: Der tödliche Dourado
programme.desc: In Argentinien macht Jeremy Wade Jagd auf ein bösartiges Raubtier, den so genannten "Flusstiger".

programme.title: Nach dem Wasser
programme.desc: Ein Erdbeben vor Sumatra löste 2004 den Tsunami aus. Der Film schildert die Umstände in der Region Aceh und wie die SOS-Kinderdörfer es schafften, Nothilfe zu leisten und bis heute mit ihren Programmen Kindern und Erwachsenen zu helfen.

programme.title: Kenia
programme.desc: Asha und Stephen sind im SOS-Kinderdorf in Nairobi aufgewachsen und haben das Beste daraus gemacht. Sie sind "The next Generation". Die Generation, die es schaffen will und auch schaffen wird.

programme.title: Waschbären, unsere neuen Nachbarn?
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

programme.title: Leben mit dem Tod
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Auf der indonesischen Insel Sulawesi dreht sich schon zu Lebzeiten der Bewohner alles die Beerdigung. Der Totenkult der Toraja kann viel Geld verschlingen, was die Bestattung verstorbener Verwandter oft auf Jahre unmöglich macht. So behalten die Angehörigen ihre Toten so lange im Haus, bis sie das Geld für die aufwendigen Feierlichkeiten haben.

programme.title: Just Cooking | Trailer
programme.desc: Just Cooking bringt Kochbegeisterten das einzigartige Paket an frischen neuen Food-Trends und junger Kreativität auf den TV. Aber auch Klassiker und traditionelle Küche, sowie kulinarische Dokumentationen und Reisevlogs werden gezeigt.

programme.title: Paris, Blitz Motorcycles
programme.desc: Fred Jourden und Hugo Jezegabel haben ihre Leidenschaft zum Beruf und zum Geschäft gemacht: In ihrer Werkstatt mitten in Paris fertigen sie kunstvoll aus alten Motorrädern neue, ganz besondere Zweiräder. Jedes Exemplar ist ein Unikat.

programme.title: Kambodscha
programme.desc: Der Japaner Kikuo Morimoto fördert in Kambodscha die traditionelle Webkunst und verschafft mit der Anpflanzung von Maulbeerbäumen und der Herstellung hochwertiger Seidenstoffe Hunderten von Menschen ein Einkommen. Er geht wie jeden Morgen durch die Reihen der 300 Frauen, die in seiner Seiden-Weberei arbeiten. Der ehemalige Kimonomaler war vor 15 Jahren, bei seiner ersten Reise nach Phnom Penh, auf die Spur der fast ausgelöschten Tradition der Seidenweberei gestoßen. Ausgelöscht während der Diktatur der Roten Khmer und dem nachfolgenden Bürgerkrieg, unter dem Kambodscha jahrzehntelang gelitten hat. Für ihr Ziel, den neuen Menschen zu schaffen, zertrümmerten die Roten Khmer im Namen eines Steinzeit-Kommunismus alles Geistige und Sinnliche im Lande. Damit verschwand beinahe auch die einmalige Kunst der Seidenherstellung. Morimoto grub die alten Rezepturen des Färbens wieder aus: rot aus dem Saft der Lackschildläuse, braun vom Sud der Kokosnussschalen, grau durch die ausgekochten Äste des Lychee-Baums. Und er studierte die in Vergessenheit geratenen, über 1200 Jahre alten Muster. 1996 gründete er schließlich eine Weberei. Im ganzen Land konnte er nur noch ein Dutzend Weberinnen aufspüren und für sein Projekt begeistern. Sie verließen ihre Dörfer und zogen mit ihm nach Siem Reap, ...

programme.title: Die Verwandlungskünstler von Dakar
programme.desc: Dakar, die Hauptstadt Senegals: Hier zu überleben, ist für viele Menschen eine Frage der Improvisation. In vielen Vierteln hat die Not einen ganz eigenen Boom hervorgebracht: Die Menschen sammeln, was andere weggeworfen haben - und wandeln diese Abfälle in Neues? um. Wir zeigen, wie alte Konservendosen in Spielzeugautos, Lampen und Koffer verwandelt werden, Kronkorken in Körbe, Motoren in Kochtöpfe, Autoreifen in Eimer. So entstehen Gebrauchsgegenstände, aber auch Spielzeuge und Möbelstücke, die in Europa bereits als Kleinkunst gehandelt werden. Der 31-Jährige Malick Mbaye weiß zu schätzen, was andere Menschen wegwerfen: Büchsen, Dosen und Flaschendeckel - oder alte Paletten. Zusammen mit seinem Kompagnon Alassane Diop, 26, bastelt er daraus mit meist improvisierten Werkzeugen Kommoden, Koffer oder Gießkannen, aber auch Spielzeug. Sogar aus Europa erhalten die beiden inzwischen Aufträge. Mit ihrer kleinen Werkstatt Soweto Village? können sie ihre Eltern und Geschwister ernähren, für eigene Familien allerdings reicht das bescheidene Einkommen nicht. Lebenstraum der beiden ist es, eines Tages alle Freunde und Verwandte beschäftigen zu können.Schon jetzt ist ihre Veranda sozialer Mittelpunkt der Nachbarschaft. Ganze Stadtteile Dakars leben von der Müll-Verwandlung. Aus Mangel an ...

programme.title: Die Marmorberge von Italien
programme.desc: Die Apuanischen Alpen im Nordwesten der Toskana beherbergen eines der größten Marmorvorkommen der Welt. Seit der Römerzeit wird hier der weltberühmte Carrara-Marmor abgebaut. Mit allen Mitteln der Technik ringt der Mensch dem Berg das wertvolle Gestein ab und transportiert es auf halsbrecherischen Wegen ins Tal, von wo aus seine Reise in die ganze Welt beginnt. Am frühen Morgen fährt der Bildhauer Renzo Maggi zum 1.300 Meter hoch gelegenen Marmorbruch von Monte Cervaiole. Bereits Michelangelo hat sich hier im 16. Jahrhundert seine gigantischen Marmorblöcke ausgesucht. Trotz moderner Technik wird die Marmorgewinnung größtenteils noch auf traditionelle Weise betrieben. Teilweise unter lebensgefährlichen Bedingungen: Extreme Wetterschwankungen und Nebel erschweren den Einsatz von schwerem Gerät. Auf halsbrecherischen Serpentinen wird die tonnenschwere Last dann hinab zum Hafen von Carrara gebracht, von wo aus der Marmor seine Reise in die ganze Welt antritt.

programme.title: Stochelo Rosenberg & Peter Beets
programme.desc: The treasured compositions of guitarist Django Reinhardt, the founding father of hot club jazz, are engraved in everyone's memory. Although Reinhardt missed two fingers of his left hand, his virtuoso technique was unrivalled. Dutch guitarist Stochelo Rosenberg and pianist Peter Beets now have the pleasure to bring Django's music back to life with their infectious improvisations.

programme.title: Wes Montgomery
programme.sub-title: Herbie Man & Sonny Sharrock - Memphis underground
programme.desc: This selection of unforgettable performances by some of the most iconic and influential jazz guitarists in history showcases these legends' unique essence. Revel in Wes Montgomery's virtuosity as he performs the captivating “Nica's Dream” in Holland in 1965, and delight in the expressive beauty of his rendition of “Here's That Rainy Day”, recorded in London in that same year. Experience the timeless appeal of Joe Pass's “You Stepped Out of a Dream” and “You Turned The Tables on Me”, recorded live in Hanover in 1975. The interplay between Jim Hall and Atilla Zoller borders on the impossible as they perform “Extensions” in Hanover in 1973. Enjoy Jim Hall's lyrical solo performance of “I'm Getting Sentimental Over You” from 1964. Witness Sonny Sharrock's avant-garde fusion of jazz and rock in an exhilarating performance of “Peanut", recorded live in France in 1970. Sharrock is joined by flutist Herbie Mann in a soulful performance of “Memphis Underground” from 1969. Immerse yourself in the magic of jazz guitar!

programme.title: Lucky Peterson & The Organization
programme.desc: Every year since 1970, the German city of Burghausen has been hosting one of the largest jazz festivals in the world. During Burghausen International Jazz Week, Burghausen becomes a 'Bavarian jazz mecca': guests from all over the world join the Burghausers to enjoy the most wonderful jazz performances as the colorful hustle and bustle of spectators and musicians shake up the city. In 2019, one of these artists is the legendary bluesman Lucky Peterson, master of the blues guitar and Hammond organ, who celebrates 50 years on stage. Peterson is accompanied by his band The Organization, augmented by the talented vocalist Tamara Tramell. In a singular performance, she offers a fascinating mix of southern soul and modern R&B, exploring the limits of blues and funk.

programme.title: Ray Charles & The Raelettes
programme.sub-title: Ray Charles and the Raelettes - North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1980, American soul legend Ray Charles brought the Raelettes and the Ray Charles Orchestra to the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague. With the full force of these two groups behind him, Charles showed why throughout his storied career he has been viewed as one of the most recognizable voices in music.

programme.title: Elizabeth Shepherd
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Gil Evans & Ornette Coleman
programme.sub-title: Gil Evans, Ornette Coleman - Schloss Ansbach
programme.desc: This program presents two concerts from Schloss Ansbach in 1978. The first concert features Gil Evans and his orchestra, consisting of Gil Evans on piano, Steve Lacy on soprano saxophone, Arthur Blythe on alto saxophone, Pit Levin on synthesizers, Earl McIntyre on trombone, Lewis Soloff on trumpet, Geoffrey Berlin on bass and Sue Evans on percussion instruments. The second concert features saxophonist Ornette Coleman at the peak of his musically expressive powers. Coleman is joined by Bern Nix on guitar, Charles Ellerbee on guitar, Albert Arnold on bass, and Shannon Jackson on drums and percussion.

programme.title: Raul Midón
programme.desc: Raul Midón appeared at 2017's Sing Jazz Festival in Singapore with double bassist Romeir Mendez and drummer Billy Williams. Blind since birth, Raul Midón is a singer, guitarist, and songwriter from New Mexico. With a vocal range as dynamic as his guitar playing and a remarkable talent for trumpet mimicry, Midón's performances transcend musical boundaries, effortlessly blending rock, jazz, folk, and Latin pop into his unique sound. He has worked with numerous legends, including Bill Withers, Herbie Hancock, Sting, and Dianne Reeves, and his album ‘Bad Ass and Blind' was nominated for a Grammy Award for Best Jazz Vocal Album in 2018. No wonder the Sing Jazz audience were ecstatic!

programme.title: Robert Glasper & Jason Moran
programme.sub-title: La Gaité Lyrique: Robert Glasper & Jason Moran
programme.desc: As part of the Blue Note Jazz Festival and Blue Note Records' 75th anniversary, pianists Robert Glasper and Jason Moran delivered a stunning jazz piano duet, resulting in an exciting exploration of the great history of jazz. An intricate knowledge of African-American music is infused with modern energy. The two musicians reinterpret the stride piano tradition through captivating original songs and personal interpretations of the music of Albert Ammons, Andrew Hill, Thelonious Monk, Ornette Coleman and Herbie Hancock.

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: John Coltrane, McCoy Tyner, Elvin Jones & Jimmy Garrison
programme.desc: The mere mention of the name John Coltrane evokes a deeply emotional, often spiritual response from even the most casual jazz fan. Dexter Gordon was a fantastic saxophonist. Miles Davis was a genius. Coltrane stood above - he was a visionary, a saint-like figure. By the standards of most jazz musicians, his life was uneventful. Sure, he had a heroin habit for a while, and Miles Davis punched him, but once he'd experienced the “spiritual awakening” described in the liner notes of his 1965 album A Love Supreme, he dedicated himself to his music with extreme single-mindedness. This broadcast of Coltrane's 1965 performance at the short-lived Belgian jazz festival in Comblain-la-Tour features Trane's classic quartet with Elvin Jones (drums), Jimmy Garrison (bass) and McCoy Tyner (piano).

programme.title: Rod Stewart
programme.desc: Roderick David Stewart was born in Highgate North London as the Second World war was coming to a close. His neighbourhood was bombed just 30 minutes before his birth, giving him the feeling that he almost didn't make it into the world. One of Rod's earliest exposures to music was with the family gatherings around the piano in which they would sing songs by the 30s baritone singer, Al Jolson. The young Rod was also caught up in the wake of Rock and Roll music that swept 50s Britain. Rod developed a love of Otis Redding and Sam Cooke and took to the Blues circuit with his first band The Dimensions. However Rod lost vocal duties to Jimmy Powell and soon left the group but fate intervened in the form of singer Long John Baldry. Baldry brought Stewart into his band The Hoochie Coochie Men, but like many of Rod's musical projects in the mid 60s it was short lived. However Baldry and Stewart were soon back together as part of Steam Packet along with Julie Driscoll. Rod had embraced the Mod look by this stage and the nickname Rod the Mod began to stick as his recognition grew. After leaving Steam Packet Rod was quickly picked up by former Yard Birds guitarist Jeff Beck. Rod had been a fan of The Yard Birds and this opportunity not only gave him a chance to sing with a hero, but also tour extensively across the US in the late 60s. Whilst on tour with Jeff Beck, Rod met guitarist Ronnie Wood, the two remained friends and when the Jeff Beck group disbanded, Rod and Ronnie became part of a new band that would be key to the success of both of their careers, Faces Despite his success with Faces, Rod released his own debut solo album An Old Raincoat Won't Ever Let You Down. The bulk of which was recorded during his time in the Jeff Beck group Things would change dramatically for Stewart as a solo artist with the release of his third solo album 1971's Every Picture Tells A Story. The album would make him the first solo artist to achieve the number 1 position in both the US and the UK. And would give him his first smash hit single Maggie May Featuring archive material, music videos “Maggie May” “In The Morning” and, exclusive insights from music critics and journalists Michael Bonner (Uncut Magazine), Hamish MacBain (Shortlist), John Aizlewood (Evening Standard) Rock Legends Rod Stewart tells the story of one of Britain's enduring rock stars.

programme.title: Daryl Hall & John Oates
programme.sub-title: Live at The Sydney Entertainment Centre
programme.desc: When Daryl Hall and John Oates took to the stage at Sydney's Entertainment Centre as the iconic bass line of ‘Maneater' began to play, the fans knew they were in for a treat. This duo may have been opening concerts with that irresistibly smooth number for years, but it never seems to lose its magic, and the crowd – an eclectic mix of teens and baby boomers alike – lapped it up. Daryl Hall and John Oates wisely reunited a few years ago after a string of solo projects, and although Oates no longer sports his signature ‘tache, they put on the kind of show that makes it hard to believe they even considered going their separate ways. Earworms like ‘I Can't Go For That', ‘Out Of Touch' and ‘Kiss On My List' were surefire reminders that these guys are absolute hit machines, and their catchy synth-soul classics probably deserve to permeate the airwaves as much today as they did decades ago. These Philly crooners still have it in bucket-loads, so this show should have everyone from diehard Daryl Hall and John Oates fans to kids of the 80's groovin' along in no time.

programme.desc: Kiss is one of the legendary groups in Hard Rock history. They have millions of fans around the world and over 100 million records sold. KISS confirms why they have been the best on the scene for nearly four decades, in a performance that made history, impressing an audience of more than 85,000 people, in a show of more than 2 hours and packed with hits, held at the Nurburgring, Germany in 2010.

programme.title: Tom Petty
programme.desc: Tom Petty was the lead singer of Tom Petty and the Heartbreakers, formed in 1976. He was also a co-founder of the late 1980s supergroup the Traveling Wilburys. He recorded many hit singles with the Heartbreakers and as a solo artist. In his career, he sold more than 80 million records worldwide, making him one of the best-selling music artists of all time. He was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2001. He was found unconscious at his home, not breathing and in full cardiac arrest, early in the morning of October 2, 2017. He was taken to the UCLA Medical Center in Santa Monica, California, where he died at 8:40 pm that evening by accidental death by a combination of pain killers.

programme.title: Janis Joplin
programme.desc: Janis Joplin was one of the most successful and widely-known female rock stars of her era. After releasing three albums, she died of a heroin overdose at the age of 27. Her fourth album, Pearl, was released in January 1971, just over three months after her death. It reached number one on the Billboard charts. Her Legacy. The big-voiced, bluesy singer dominated the stage, forged her own path and paved the way for the female singers who followed.

programme.title: Ivan Fischer, Budapest Festival Orchestra & Richard Goode
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Symphonies and Piano Concerto No. 4
programme.desc: Iván Fischer leads his Budapest Festival Orchestra (BFO) in a concert program dedicated to the music of Ludwig van Beethoven. The program opens with the composer's Symphony No. 1 in C major, Op. 21. Afterward, Fischer conducts Beethoven's Piano Concerto No. 4 in G major, Op. 58, in which Richard Goode features as the soloist. The acclaimed American pianist (1943) is known for his interpretations of the Beethoven repertoire. Goode recorded all five Beethoven piano concertos with the BFO and Fischer, earning him exceptional critical acclaim and a Grammy Award nomination. As an encore, Goode performs the Sarabande from J. S. Bach's Partita in B-flat major, BWV 825. The program closes with Beethoven's famous Symphony No. 5 in C minor, Op. 67. This performance was recorded at the Béla Bartók National Concert Hall in Budapest, Hungary, on January 29, 2017.

programme.title: Quatuor Ebène
programme.desc: Renowned French string quartet Quatuor Ébène marked the 250th birth anniversary of Ludwig van Beethoven (1770-1827) with a remarkable project: recording all of the great composer's sixteen string quartets. For five years, violinists Pierre Colombet and Gabriel Le Magadure, violist Marie Chilemme, and cellist Raphaël Merlin immersed themselves in Beethoven's 650 pages of sheet music. Their efforts culminated in the performance of the composer's complete repertoire for string quartet, which covers three decades of Beethoven's musical creativity, during six impressive concerts at Philharmonie de Paris in the autumn of 2020. Quatuor Ébène explored every facet of Beethoven's string quartet repertoire: from the youthful Opus 18 string quartets to the Razumovsky, Harp, and Serioso quartets (Opus 59, 74, and 95) from his middle period, and finally, the depth of his late quartets (Opus 127 to 135). This program features Quatuor Ébène performing Beethoven's String Quartet No. 1 in F major, Op. 18, No. 1 String Quartet No. 10 in E-flat major, Op. 74, "Harp" and String Quartet No. 9 in C major, Op. 59, No. 3, "Razumovsky". This concert performance was recorded at Philharmonie de Paris on October 13, 2020.

programme.title: Martha Argerich, Evgeny Kissin, Theodosia Ntokou & Cristina Marton-Argerich
programme.sub-title: Martha Argerich – A Birthday Celebration - II
programme.desc: On the occasion of her 80th birthday, Argentinian pianist Martha Argerich explored repertoire for piano and violin in this wonderful concert, recorded at Château de Chantilly, France. The ‘Grande Dame' of the piano is joined by various renowned artists, including pianists Evgeny Kissin, Theodosia Ntokou, and Cristina Marton-Argerich, and violinist Maxim Vengerov. On the program are Dmitri Shostakovich's Concertino for two pianos, Op. 94 Frédéric Chopin's Impromptu No. 3, Op. 51, Polonaise No. 6, Op. 53 “Heroic”, and Waltz No. 6, Op. 64 No. 1 Camille Saint-Saëns's Polonaise for two pianos, Op. 77 César Franck's Sonata for violin and piano in A major and Fritz Kreisler's Liebesleid and Schön Rosmarin. This performance was recorded on June 12, 2021.

programme.title: Václav Luks & Collegium 1704
programme.desc: J. S. Bach's six Brandenburg Concerto's belong to his best-known works. The composer wrote these concertos between 1711 and 1720 and dedicated them in 1721 to Christian Ludwig, Margrave of Brandenburg. In celebration of the pieces' 300th anniversary, Czech harpsichordist and conductor Václav Luks and the renowned Baroque ensemble Collegium 1704 recorded all six Brandenburg Concertos on historical instruments in 2021. The concertos are based on the Italian concerto grosso form, in which a group of solo instruments is set against a large ensemble. Bach's Brandenburg Concertos feature remarkable combinations of solo instruments and virtuoso solos. This performance was recorded at the Hall of Mirrors in the Köthen Castle, Germany.

programme.title: Kinderstube Wildnis Bei den Bären
programme.desc: Mitten im Winterschlaf - versteckt unter einer dichten Schneedecke - kommen die drei kleinen Schwarzbären Sam, Sophie und Sybil zur Welt. Ihre ersten Wochen verbringen die noch nackten und blinden Babys im Schutz der geräumigen Höhle. Sobald die Tage länger werden, lugen die inzwischen flauschigen Bärenkinder zum ersten Mal aus dem Bau und für die ausgehungerte Bärin wird es Zeit, die Reserven wieder aufzufüllen. Obwohl im Wald viele Gefahren lauern, muss sie bald aufbrechen. Für den Bären-Nachwuchs sind die Ausflüge die reinsten Abenteuer. Während die Mutter besorgt nach Raubtieren Ausschau hält, toben sie fröhlich durchs Unterholz. Neben der Suche nach Essbarem hat die Mutter es nicht leicht, ihre verspielte Rasselbande zusammenzuhalten. Ohne den Schutz der Mutter sind die noch viel zu kleinen Bärchen aber hoffnungslos verloren. Ausgewachsene Schwarzbären haben kaum natürliche Feinde, aber als Jungtiere sind sie für Adler und Wölfe leichte Beute. Nur zwanzig Prozent überleben überhaupt den ersten Geburtstag. Plötzlich bricht nur unweit der Höhle auch noch Feuer im Wald aus...

programme.title: Delfine Hautnah Dreamteams
programme.desc: Im ersten Teil geht es vor allem um die sozialen Strukturen innerhalb einer Delfinschule Großer Tümmler und zwischen Delfinen aus verschiedenen Gruppen. Schon sehr kleine Delfine werden zur Jagd mitgenommen und an den richtigen Gebrauch ihres eigenen Bio- Sonars herangeführt, denn das muss erst erlernt werden. Dabei offenbart sich, dass sich Delfine verschiedener Regionen auf Beute spezialisieren und je nach Beutetier besondere Jagdtechniken anwenden, die von Generation zu Generation weitergegeben werden. Unter Umständen werden sogar Ziel führende Koalitionen mit anderen Meeresbewohnern eingegangen, zum Beispiel mit Stachelrochen. Bei den Großen Tümmlern leben Männchen und Weibchen in getrennten Gruppen. Mittels der Kameraspione können die Werbe- und Paarungsrituale der Großen Tümmler genau beobachtet werden. Die zweite, näher betrachtete Delfinart sind die Spinner- Delfine, bekannt durch ihre waghalsigen Sprünge. Diese Delfinart ist anderen Gruppen der gleichen Art weitaus aufgeschlossener als Große Tümmler und schließt sich gelegentlich zu riesigen Mega- Delfinschulen zusammen, die gemeinsam auf Beutezüge gehen.

programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

programme.title: Leben mit dem Tod
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Auf der indonesischen Insel Sulawesi dreht sich schon zu Lebzeiten der Bewohner alles die Beerdigung. Der Totenkult der Toraja kann viel Geld verschlingen, was die Bestattung verstorbener Verwandter oft auf Jahre unmöglich macht. So behalten die Angehörigen ihre Toten so lange im Haus, bis sie das Geld für die aufwendigen Feierlichkeiten haben.

programme.title: Just Cooking | Trailer
